<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Wikidata-Onboarding</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css"
          href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/semantic-ui/2.3.3/semantic.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">
    <style>
        .large.text {
            font-size: 12px;
        }
    </style>
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.3.1.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
<input id="mturkConfig" type="hidden" value="{{mturkConfig}}">
<h1></h1>
<div class="ui grid">
    <div class="one wide column">
    </div>
    <div class="seven wide column">
        <img class="ui medium left floated image" src="/img/Wide.png">
    </div>
    <div class="seven wide column">
        <img class="ui medium right floated image" src="/img/Fub-logo-trans.png">
    </div>
    <div class="one wide column">
    </div>
</div>
<div class="ui grid">
    <div class="three wide column"></div>
    <div class="ten wide column" style="font-size: 18px;">
        <p>Wikidata, a collaborative community knowledge base, is a sister project of Wikipedia. The goal of Wikidata is
            to provide a central repository for structured data, largely similar to what Wikipedia provides for
            encyclopedic content. Wikidata is operated by the same organization, the Wikimedia Foundation, as Wikipedia,
            and both communities have a significant overlap and collaborate intensively. </p>
        <br>
        <p>One of the big challenges of Wikidata is quality, and in particular, completeness. Wikidata operates under an
            open schema, meaning anyone can add nearly any kind of data. Consequently, even knowledgeable editors may
            lose track of which properties are relevant to a given entity of specific class (such as a ‘scientific
            article’ or ‘football player’)..</p>
        <br>
        {{#shouldIncludeRecoinText}}
            <p>
                Recoin is an analytics and recommender tool for understanding and improving the completeness of
                Wikidata.
                The goal of Recoin is to automate the identification of relevant properties for an entity, and to
                visualize
                the completeness degree of an entity.
            </p>
        {{/shouldIncludeRecoinText}}
        <p>
            For this HIT, which will consist of adding relevant data to a Wikidata entry, you will have 10 minutes.
            After the 10 minutes have elapsed, we will provide you with a short questionnaire. Click the ‘Proceed’
            button below for a HIT briefing and tutorial, after which you can choose to start the HIT.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="three wide column"></div>
</div>
<div class="ui grid">
    <div class="three wide column"></div>
    <div class="ten wide column">
        <nav>
            <a href="/briefing">
                <div style="float:right;">
                    <button class="ui button">
                        Proceed
                    </button>
                </div>
            </a>
        </nav>
    </div>
</div>
<script type="text/javascript">
    var mTurkConfig = JSON.parse($('#mturkConfig').val());
    localStorage.setItem('assignmentID', mTurkConfig.assignmentId);
    localStorage.setItem('workerID', mTurkConfig.workerId);
    localStorage.setItem('hitID', mTurkConfig.hitId);
    localStorage.setItem('turkSubmitTo', mTurkConfig.turkSubmitTo);
    localStorage.setItem('condition', mTurkConfig.condition);
</script>
</body>
</html>
